{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01SvHjKJevJb2VrFk5yhe1Hk","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The error is `TypeError: Cannot read properties of undefined (reading 'errorCode')`. This means `(err as AnchorError).error` is undefined. The error isn't an AnchorError, it's probably a different kind of error.\n\nLooking at the cancel_match instruction:\n```rust\npub struct CancelMatch<'info> {\n    #[account(mut)]\n    pub creator: Signer<'info>,\n    #[account(\n        mut,\n        close = creator,\n        seeds = [b\"match\", creator.key().as_ref()],\n        bump = coinflip_match.bump,\n    )]\n    pub coinflip_match: Account<'info, CoinflipMatch>,\n    pub system_program: Program<'info, System>,\n}\n```\n\nThe `cancelMatch` function calls with creator as the signer. After join_match, the match is in Locked phase. The handler calls `transition(coinflip_match.phase, RoundPhase::Refunded)` which should fail because Locked → Refunded IS actually a valid transition! Looking at the lifecycle, that transition is allowed, so the issue must be something else.\n\nActually, I see the real problem now — the cancel_match handler uses `transition(phase, Refunded)` and Locked → Refunded is a valid transition, so the instruction would proceed. Then Anchor's `close = creator` would close the account and refund everything to the creator, including the opponent's deposit. The seed constraint `seeds = [b\"match\", creator.key().as_ref()]` ensures only the creator can cancel, but that means they'd receive both their own and the opponent's funds when the account closes.\n\nThe bug is that cancel_match should only work in Waiting phase, not Locked. The transition rules allow Locked → Refunded because timeout_cancel uses that same transition, but cancel_match needs an additional phase check. The handler just calls `transition()` without verifying the phase is Waiting, so it incorrectly permits cancellation from Locked state — that's a program bug, not a test issue. using `transition()` which also allows Locked→Refunded (for timeout_cancel), the handler became too permissive. I need to add an explicit check to ensure cancel_match only works from the Waiting phase, restoring the original behavior before rebuilding and retesting.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":389,"cache_read_input_tokens":159828,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":389},"output_tokens":10,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"26c7f4cc-b2b2-41aa-85e9-beee2a3d95f1","uuid":"207d14c1-f66b-4d42-bae3-f1069da9edb5"}
