{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"This session is being continued from a previous conversation that ran out of context. The summary below covers the earlier portion of the conversation.\n\nAnalysis:\nLet me chronologically analyze the conversation to capture all important details.\n\n1. The user initiated an autonomous spec implementation loop for iteration 14 of spec 004-shared-infrastructure. The spec is about shared infrastructure for an RNG gaming platform on Solana.\n\n2. The first unchecked checklist item is the test rewrite: rewriting `solana/tests/coinflip.ts` bankrun tests for the new 3-tx program flow (create → join+request → claim+read).\n\n3. I spawned 3 parallel Task agents to explore:\n   - Coinflip program source (all instruction files, state, lib, error)\n   - Shared crate modules (lifecycle, timeout, vrf_orao, escrow, etc.)\n   - Existing tests, config files, platform program\n\n4. The user's response was cut off due to output token limit. They said \"Continue from where you left off.\"\n\n5. I then:\n   - Checked dependencies (pnpm install needed)\n   - Installed node dependencies\n   - Verified build artifacts exist\n   - Checked the coinflip IDL structure\n   - Checked solana-bankrun Clock export signature\n   - Checked anchor-bankrun package format (CJS)\n\n6. Wrote the complete new test file with:\n   - Mock VRF randomness handling\n   - Tests for all instructions: initialize_config, create_match, join_match, claim_payout, cancel_match, timeout_cancel\n   - Full lifecycle tests\n   - Used `__dirname` (CJS pattern) initially\n\n7. First error: `__dirname is not defined in ES module scope` - the package.json has `\"type\": \"module\"` so Node treats files as ESM. Fixed by switching to `import.meta.url` pattern.\n\n8. Second issue: Segmentation fault when running tests with `npx mocha`. Extensive debugging:\n   - Minimal tests work fine\n   - startAnchor works\n   - Individual instruction flows work in isolation\n   - 8+ contexts in stress test work\n   - The segfault is specific to the full coinflip.ts file\n\n9. Solution: Using `tsx/cjs` as a mocha require. `npx mocha --require tsx/cjs` works perfectly. Installed tsx as dev dependency.\n\n10. Found one test failure: \"rejects cancel after Locked (InvalidTransition)\" - the cancel_match handler was using `shared::lifecycle::transition(phase, Refunded)` which allows Locked→Refunded (valid for timeout_cancel but wrong for cancel_match).\n\n11. Fixed the cancel_match.rs handler to use explicit `require!(phase == Waiting, CannotCancel)` instead of `transition()`.\n\n12. Updated test expectation from \"InvalidTransition\" to \"CannotCancel\".\n\n13. Updated Anchor.toml test script from `ts-mocha` to `mocha --require tsx/cjs`.\n\n14. Final result: 31 tests passing (26 coinflip + 5 platform).\n\n15. Was about to check off the spec item and update history when the summary was requested.\n\nKey files modified:\n- tests/coinflip.ts - complete rewrite\n- programs/coinflip/src/instructions/cancel_match.rs - bug fix\n- Anchor.toml - test runner change\n- package.json - added tsx dev dependency\n\nThe checklist item being worked on:\n```\n- [ ] [test] Rewrite `solana/tests/coinflip.ts` bankrun tests for new 3-tx program\n```\n\nAfter this test item, 2 more items remain:\n- Re-run scripts/sync-idl\n- Drop MagicBlock VRF references\n\nSummary:\n1. Primary Request and Intent:\n   The user is running an autonomous spec implementation loop (iteration 14 of 16) for spec `004-shared-infrastructure`. The task is to implement the FIRST unchecked checklist item from the spec's Implementation Checklist. The first unchecked item is:\n   \n   `[test] Rewrite solana/tests/coinflip.ts bankrun tests for new 3-tx program — Setup: deploy coinflip + platform programs with mock-vrf feature, initialize configs. Tests: create_match (phase=Waiting, escrow correct, pause check), join_match (phase=Locked, escrow doubled, vrf_request_key set, resolve_deadline set), claim_payout with mock randomness (reads mock account, derives winner HEADS/TAILS, fee math correct, treasury transfer, profile CPI for both players, MatchSettled event emitted, match PDA closed), cancel_match (Waiting-only, full refund), timeout_cancel (after resolve_deadline expired AND VRF unfulfilled, permissionless, both players refunded), error cases (invalid phase transitions, double-claim, unauthorized, self-join, claim with unfulfilled randomness rejected, timeout_cancel rejected when VRF IS fulfilled — must claim instead). Target: all tests green. Verify: anchor test --skip-local-validator.`\n\n   Rules: Work autonomously, no questions. Pick first unchecked item, implement it, run targeted check, check it off if passing, append to history. Do NOT commit.\n\n2. Key Technical Concepts:\n   - Solana Anchor framework (v0.32.1) with bankrun testing\n   - Mock VRF pattern: `mock-vrf` feature flag makes Orao VRF CPI a no-op; `read_orao_randomness` reads raw 32 bytes from account data\n   - 3-tx coinflip flow: create_match → join_match (+ VRF request) → claim_payout (reads VRF at claim time)\n   - RoundPhase enum (Waiting, Active, Locked, Resolving, Settled, Refunded) replaces old u8 phase constants\n   - Shared crate (`rng-shared`) provides lifecycle, escrow, fees, timeout, pause, VRF, CPI helpers\n   - `anchor-bankrun` + `solana-bankrun` for testing (BankrunProvider, startAnchor, Clock manipulation)\n   - Node 24 native TS type stripping (ESM mode with `\"type\": \"module\"`)\n   - `tsx/cjs` mocha require for reliable test execution on this platform (avoids segfault)\n   - Permissionless timeout_cancel: any signer can trigger after deadline IF VRF is unfulfilled\n   - Either player can trigger claim_payout — payout always goes to derived winner regardless of caller\n\n3. Files and Code Sections:\n\n   - **`/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/tests/coinflip.ts`** (COMPLETE REWRITE)\n     - Replaced old test file (used resolve_match, oracle authority, u8 phases) with new 3-tx flow tests\n     - 26 tests covering: initialize_config (1), create_match (4), join_match (3), claim_payout (9), cancel_match (3), timeout_cancel (3), full lifecycle (3)\n     - Key patterns: Mock VRF with `context.setAccount()` to write randomness data, `Clock` from solana-bankrun for time warping, `import.meta.url` for ESM __dirname, `JSON.stringify(m.phase)` for enum comparison\n     - Mock randomness: HEADS = Buffer with byte[0]=2 (2%2=0=HEADS, non-zero=fulfilled), TAILS = byte[0]=1, UNFULFILLED = all zeros\n     - Uses `tsx/cjs` require for mocha (avoids Node 24 segfault with native TS)\n\n   - **`/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/programs/coinflip/src/instructions/cancel_match.rs`** (BUG FIX)\n     - Fixed regression where `transition(phase, Refunded)` allowed Locked→Refunded (valid for timeout_cancel but wrong for cancel)\n     - Changed from `use rng_shared::lifecycle::{transition, RoundPhase}` to `use rng_shared::lifecycle::RoundPhase` + `use crate::error::CoinflipError`\n     - Replaced `transition(coinflip_match.phase, RoundPhase::Refunded)?;` with explicit `require!(coinflip_match.phase == RoundPhase::Waiting, CoinflipError::CannotCancel);`\n     - Final file content:\n     ```rust\n     use anchor_lang::prelude::*;\n     use rng_shared::lifecycle::RoundPhase;\n     use crate::error::CoinflipError;\n     use crate::state::CoinflipMatch;\n\n     #[derive(Accounts)]\n     pub struct CancelMatch<'info> {\n         #[account(mut)]\n         pub creator: Signer<'info>,\n         #[account(mut, close = creator, seeds = [b\"match\", creator.key().as_ref()], bump = coinflip_match.bump)]\n         pub coinflip_match: Account<'info, CoinflipMatch>,\n         pub system_program: Program<'info, System>,\n     }\n\n     pub fn handler(ctx: Context<CancelMatch>) -> Result<()> {\n         let coinflip_match = &ctx.accounts.coinflip_match;\n         require!(coinflip_match.phase == RoundPhase::Waiting, CoinflipError::CannotCancel);\n         Ok(())\n     }\n     ```\n\n   - **`/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/Anchor.toml`** (MODIFIED)\n     - Changed test script from `pnpm exec ts-mocha -p ./tsconfig.json -t 1000000 tests/**/*.ts` to `pnpm exec mocha --require tsx/cjs -t 1000000 tests/**/*.ts`\n\n   - **`/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/solana/package.json`** (MODIFIED via pnpm add)\n     - Added `tsx` as dev dependency for mocha require\n\n   - **Spec file**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/specs/004-shared-infrastructure/spec.md` - Read to identify current checklist item\n   - **History file**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/specs/004-shared-infrastructure/history.md` - Read to understand prior iterations (1-13 completed)\n   - All coinflip program source files were read via Task agents (state.rs, lib.rs, all instruction files, error.rs)\n   - All shared crate modules were read via Task agents (lifecycle.rs, timeout.rs, vrf_orao.rs, escrow.rs, fees.rs, pause.rs, cpi.rs, commit_reveal.rs, constants.rs, tiers.rs)\n   - Platform program files read (lib.rs, state.rs) for understanding CPI interface\n\n4. Errors and Fixes:\n   - **`__dirname is not defined in ES module scope`**: Package.json has `\"type\": \"module\"`, so Node treats .ts as ESM. Fixed by using `import.meta.url` + `fileURLToPath` + `dirname` pattern instead of bare `__dirname`.\n   \n   - **Segmentation fault (exit code 139)** when running tests with `npx mocha` (Node 24 native TS): The native solana-bankrun binary crashes when loading the full coinflip.ts file through Node's native TS type stripping. Minimal test files work fine. Extensive debugging: verified startAnchor works, individual flows work, stress test with 8+ contexts works, imports work. Root cause appears to be Node 24's native TS type stripping + native addon interaction. Fixed by installing `tsx` as devDependency and using `npx mocha --require tsx/cjs` which handles TS compilation properly.\n   \n   - **Test failure: \"rejects cancel